            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Since  #4448, <kbd>Shift</kbd> + <kbd>Ins</kbd> in insert mode does not work (like #10223), while <kbd>\"</kbd><kbd>+</kbd>/<kbd>*</kbd><kbd>p</kbd> in normal mode works.\r\n\r\n<!-- Before reporting: search existing issues and check the FAQ. -->\r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`: NVIM v0.4.0-1856-g82d52b229df7\r\nBuild type: RelWithDebInfo\r\nLuaJIT 2.0.5\r\n- `vim -u DEFAULTS` (version: 8.1.1401) behaves differently? yes (`+` and `*` registers are unablable though)\r\n- Operating system/version: Debian 10.0\r\n- Terminal name/version: GNOME Terminal 3.30.2 using VTE 0.54.2 +GNUTLS\r\n- `$TERM`: `xterm-256color`\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\n\r\nCopy the followuing two lines\r\n```\r\na\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nand then `nvim -u NORC`\r\n<kbd>\"</kbd><kbd>+</kbd><kbd>P</kbd>\r\n<kbd>\"</kbd><kbd>*</kbd><kbd>P</kbd>\r\n<kbd>O</kbd> <kbd>Shift</kbd>+<kbd>Ins</kbd>\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\n```\r\na^M^M\r\na\r\n\r\na\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n`od -x` gives\r\n```\r\n0000000 0d61 0a0d 0a61 610a 0a0a 000a\r\n0000013\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\n```\r\na\r\n\r\na\r\n\r\na\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n",
