            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "From https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/22807#issuecomment-1488648552\r\n\r\n> It is problematic to terminate a paste with characters that may be included(`CTRL-c`) in the text being pasted. There are known attacks that paste content other than the user's selected text in a paste-from-browser scenario. Therefore, this attack may succeed if we terminate the paste with `CTRL-c`, etc.\r\n\r\n> IMO: The preferred solution to this problem is when `tinput_read_cb()` finishes with `input->past != 0`, set a timer that will terminate the paste if the next sequence does not arrive with a long enough timeout(e.g. 5sec).\r\n            ",
